user.name: WIZZ design
user.bio:
WIZZdesign is a animation studio founded in 2003 by the QUAD Group, and it quickly became a true creative solution for the production of commercials and music videos in Paris. WIZZdesign is a boutique and graphic laboratory that has developed its own directors during the past decade, and is dedicated to its artists (film, print, press, events), giving them considerable resources at their disposal to produce their work.

In 2009 WIZZdesign was picked up by Blacklist in New York, a graphic production house started by PSYOP that represents the only most creative studios. WIZZ has also recently touched down in England, partnering with Friend London, a highly creative and selective production company who works with notable directors such as Alphabetical Order and Buck.
--
Wizzdesign est un studio graphique fondé en 2003 par le groupe QUAD production, il apparaît rapidement comme une véritable solution créative pour la production de films publicitaires et de clips à Paris. C’est une boutique, un laboratoire graphique qui a su développer ses propres réalisateurs au cours de ces dix dernières années. Wizzdesign est un lieu dédié aux artistes (film, print, presse, event) avec des ressources considérables mises à leur disposition pour la production de leurs images.
Wizzdesign est repéré en 2009 par Blacklist à New York, maison de production graphique montée par PSYOP représentant les studios les plus créatifs du moment et met un pied depuis peu en Angleterre en fondant Friend à Londres, maison de production select travaillant notamment avec des réalisateurs comme Alphabetical Order & BUCK.

data.name: A Tour Of Espioña
data.description:
There was this board game back when I was a child. It was pretty forgettable by all accounts, yet for some reason the setting—a close grouping of embassies, tailormade for espionage shenanigans—stuck in my mind, and I used to imagine myself as one of the game characters, stalking the streets.

So here is my recreation of the game board, and here is an animated tour showing what it might be like to walk those streets.

Maybe I should do a night-time version...

You can see higher-res stills on DeviantArt: http://default-cube.deviantart.com/gallery/54740632/Spy-Ring

Also see an aerial view: https://vimeo.com/129949468

data.name: The Font-Pre ecodistrict
data.description:
Topaze agency asked us to make a video of the new ecodistrict project from the famous french builder Bouygues Immobilier.

The brief was to focus on the concept and characteristics of the urbanistic project. For this we invited the arquitect who designed the whole project, to explain his vision of the project and its rôle into the city.

Tigrelab had been in charge of the complete production, from the original idea, the shooting and the post production.


Credits

Original Concept: Topaze / Tigrelab
Direction & Art Direction: Tigrelab
Production: Tigrelab
DOP: Mickael Lemercier
Sound Engineer: Maxime Gavaudan
3D:Alex Palazzi, Federico Gonzalez, Mathieu Felix
Compositing: Joan Molins
Soundtrack: Romain Collinet

We pursue different lines of action and, therefore, we are currently developing interactive projects in which images and audiovisuals are integrated with generative environments.
